==English==

===Noun===
'''withers''' 
# The part of the [[back]] of a [[draft]] [[animal]] or [[horse]] that is the [[highest]], between the [[shoulder blades]]

====Usage notes====
Although this noun refers to one object, there is no corresponding singular form for this word, so it is always treated as a plural noun (using ''are'' instead of ''is'' in a sentence, for example).

====Derived terms====
*[[fistulous withers]]
*[[wither-wrung]]
*[[wring one's withers]]

